âœ… DisposableEffect is used for:

Attaching something when the composable enters the screen
(e.g., start listener, register callback)

Removing it automatically when the composable leaves the screen
(e.g., stop listener, unregister callback)


ğŸ¯ Super Simple One-Line Definition
*************************************
ğŸ‘‰ DisposableEffect runs when the key changes AND allows you to clean up when the composable leaves the UI.


ğŸ§  When to use DisposableEffect?
*********************************
Use it when you need:

âœ”ï¸ Start a listener / observer
âœ”ï¸ Register a broadcast receiver
âœ”ï¸ Start location updates / sensor updates
âœ”ï¸ Register callbacks
âœ”ï¸ And most importantly â†’ stop them in onDispose()

ğŸ’¡ Very Important Rules
âœ”ï¸ You CANNOT run suspend functions inside DisposableEffect.